# Maintenance & Cleanup

Rules for keeping a codebase healthy over time. Code rots if left alone. These routines ensure every project stays clean, up-to-date, and free of legacy debt - whether maintained by a solo developer or a large team.

> All numeric values (cadences, percentages, durations) in this file are `[DEFAULT]` - adjust to your team's rhythm and project size.

---

## The Rule

**Every codebase has regular maintenance, just like a car has oil changes. It should be scheduled, not ad-hoc.**

---

## Adding New Functionality

When adding a new feature, follow this exact checklist BEFORE writing any code:

### Pre-Implementation Checklist

**Principle:** Before writing any code for a new feature or change, verify that the foundation is solid - understand the existing patterns, check for reusable pieces, and plan the integration.

[REFERENCE] Pre-implementation checklist:

```
1. LOCATE where it belongs
   - Which folder in the project structure? (see project-structure.md)
   - Which existing files does it touch?
   - Does a similar pattern already exist in the codebase? (reuse it)

2. PLAN the interfaces
   - What are the inputs and outputs?
   - What types/interfaces are needed?
   - What API endpoints (if any)?
   - What database changes (if any)?

3. CHECK for reuse
   - Does a utility/helper already exist for part of this? (use it, don't duplicate)
   - Does this belong in an existing service file or need a new one?
   - Can an existing component be extended or does it need a new one?

4. WRITE layers in sequence
   a. Types/interfaces first
   b. Database model/migration (if needed)
   c. Business logic (services/lib)
   d. API handler (if needed)
   e. UI component (if needed)
   f. Tests per `testing.md`: SHOULD add/update when a harness exists; otherwise only when the user asks
```

### After-Implementation Checklist

```
After the feature works:

- [ ] Follows naming conventions (naming.md) - no non-idiomatic abbreviations, descriptive names
- [ ] Follows code patterns (code-patterns.md) - correct anatomy for functions/components/handlers
- [ ] Follows formatting (code-formatting.md) - linter passes, imports ordered
- [ ] No duplicate logic - fix in task scope; **ask user before** extracting shared utilities outside scope
- [ ] No hardcoded values - magic numbers extracted to constants, URLs from env
- [ ] Error handling complete - all failure paths handled with user-friendly messages
- [ ] Loading states - every async operation has loading/error/success states in UI
- [ ] Types are correct - no `any` without justification
- [ ] Tests per `testing.md`: SHOULD add/update when a harness exists; otherwise only when the user asks
- [ ] Documentation updated - JSDoc on exported functions; README if behavior changed; docs/ if setup/env/architecture changed (see documentation.md)
```

