## Technical Debt Rules

### Identifying Debt

**Principle:** Technical debt is anything that slows down future development. Identify it by category so you can prioritize what to fix.

[REFERENCE] Common categories of technical debt:

- Duplicated logic (copy-pasted instead of shared)
- Missing types (using type escape hatches or no types)
- Missing tests (working code but untested)
- Hardcoded values (magic numbers, inline URLs)
- Outdated patterns (old way of doing things, before a better pattern was established)
- Over-engineering (abstraction nobody uses, premature optimization)
- Missing error handling (happy path only)
- Missing loading/error states in UI

### Tracking Debt

```
1. Create an issue for every known debt item
2. Tag it: "tech-debt"
3. Prioritize: critical (causes bugs) -> high (slows development) -> low (cosmetic)
4. Allocate regular time to debt reduction (don't let it stack indefinitely)
5. Review and address debt items periodically - the cadence depends on your project's pace
```

### Fixing Debt

```
Rules:
  - Fix debt in SEPARATE PRs from feature work (easier to review, revert, and track)
  - Each debt PR does ONE thing (rename, extract utility, add types, add tests)
  - Verify all tests pass after each debt fix
  - Update the debt tracking issue when fixed
```

